    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, led by the elite matchup profile of **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88). Facing Ryne Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a potent combination of a 16% park boost and favorable winds, cementing his status as the cornerstone of today\u2019s lineup. Joining him in the top tier are **Kyle Tucker** (72.86) and **Josh Lowe** (65.92), who both capitalize on prime hitting conditions. **Josh Lowe** specifically receives a significant 14% lift from a dynamic platoon edge, while **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.20) warrants a strong start due to Justin Wrobleski\u2019s slow delivery, which creates a prime opportunity to chase our critical stolen base needs.\n\nWhile our core remains strong, the bench decisions were tight. **Marcell Ozuna** (51.75) was the most difficult exclusion, finishing just shy of the 52-point threshold needed to displace our lower-utility slots. While **Marcell Ozuna** offers solid floor potential, the optimizer favored the specific park factors and situational platoon advantages enjoyed by **Coby Mayo** and **Liam Hicks**. We must remain vigilant regarding the current \"Lineup Pending\" status for all players; specifically, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Jorge Polanco** face the daunting task of matching up against Paul Skenes and Justin Wrobleski respectively. Their high SP-skill penalties (-19%) necessitate that we closely monitor the final batting orders, as any downward shift in the lineup could quickly push these marginal starts below our efficiency floor.",
